The paper discusses benchmarking of machine learning approaches, specifically genetic programming and symbolic regression, on regression problems. This falls under the category of machine learning, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category as it covers a broad range of machine learning topics, including regression. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as it covers topics related to intelligent systems, including machine learning. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as it covers topics related to neural networks and evolutionary algorithms, which are used in some of the approaches discussed in the paper. cs.DM (Data Mining) is relevant as it covers topics related to extracting knowledge from data, which is the goal of the benchmarking study. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still relevant as it covers topics related to control systems, which can be applied to machine learning.
